---

<section id="sustainability" class="sustainability section-pad">
  <div class="container sustainability__layout">
    <div class="sustainability__lead reveal">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Emissions are becoming a market requirement, not just a metric.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="sustainability__body reveal">
      <blockquote>
        <span class="sustainability__quote-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</span>
        We are adopting green steel technologies to boost access to European markets.
        <cite>— Ayman El Ashry, Group Chairman</cite>
      </blockquote>
      <p>
        As carbon border rules tighten across the EU, decarbonized steel is shifting from
        a reputational choice to a condition of export. ashrysteel's investment in cleaner
        production is built around that reality — access to the markets our customers'
        projects increasingly answer to.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .sustainability__layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .sustainability__lead {
    max-width: 34rem;
  }

  .sustainability__body {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  blockquote {
    position: relative;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .sustainability__quote-mark {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-blue);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  blockquote cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-ink-faint);
  }

  .sustainability__body > p {
    color: var(--color-ink-dim);
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .sustainability__layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.3fr;
      gap: var(--space-3xl);
    }
  }
</style>
